### Microcopy Strategy (Perception Optimization)

The section label changes based on confidence tier:

| Confidence | Top Similarity | Label |
|-----------|---------------|-------|
| `high` | >= 0.55 | "Ideas in the same orbit" |
| `medium` | >= 0.40 | "You might also explore" |
| `low` | >= 0.30 | "More from the community" |
| `none` | N/A | (do not render component) |

**Why these specific labels:**
- "Ideas in the same orbit" -- uses the space/universe metaphor already present in your platform (Universe view, galaxies, stars, wormholes). This feels intentional and brand-aligned. It says "these ideas are cosmically connected" without claiming AI magic
- "You might also explore" -- lower commitment, invitational language
- "More from the community" -- honest fallback that still provides value as general browsing

### Display Count Strategy

- **High confidence**: Show up to 5 results
- **Medium confidence**: Show up to 3 results
- **Low confidence**: Show up to 2 results
- **Never show 1 result** -- a single recommendation looks fragile. If only 1 match passes the filter, show nothing

This is a critical perception hack: fewer, better results feel more intelligent than many mediocre ones.

